sentences: Paul Ramsier (September 23, 1927 – January 31, 2021) was a classical composer most noted for his contributions to the bass literature.

The Divertimento Concertante and three subsequent works—Road to Hamelin, Eusebius Revisited, and Silent Movie—have since become bass standards, and are regarded as the most performed compositions for bass and orchestra since 1965.
